covered: Valid Deletion scenarios including multiple success paths (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC07, TC11, TC12, TC20)
Error handling and edge cases (TC08, TC14, TC15, TC16)
Handling of optional query parameters and combinations (TC02–TC05, TC13, TC05)
gaps: Authorization completeness for all edge cases beyond 401 (e.g., 403 Forbidden) is not explicitly tested
Caching behavior and header validation (ETag, Cache-Control) not covered
Pagination is not applicable to a single account delete but is not explicitly exercised for large datasets beyond TC07
Explicit testing for soft-delete semantics vs hard-delete not clearly documented beyond 204 and state changes
recommendations: Add tests to cover 403 Forbidden scenarios to ensure proper handling when user lacks rights even with valid authentication
Add tests asserting caching headers and ETag behavior where applicable to verify caching policies
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests (e.g., multiple rapid deletes) to validate resilience
Clarify and test soft-delete vs hard-delete semantics explicitly if applicable, and verify audit/logging outcomes
Consider explicit pagination-related tests if future endpoints evolve to batch operations or list-related deletions
